<@503044914016419840>
-----------------------
basic rundown for HoH guide in CN (Not for sharing)
Advantagess:
1.  Ice team was always good at short rotation, what's different with HoH is that **she does more damage in both small or big rotation**
2.  Even that she has SP problem, but in actual gameplay **her rotation is smoother than we imagined** (As for my own experience, the 'omg no sp damage bad' situation didn't happen in red lotus)
3.  In abyss, she dominates Benares and Helicopter, Hepha and Fox hasnt appear yet but we can assume she will do good, since in Benares, S0 HoH overpowers SS SW, **the higher the disturbance, the better performance HoH can be**
4.  In MA (imagine triple SSS), her **ability to trigger multiple TF** is really good, **she can deal with a lot of boss** now, and without doubt she took the top score of SSS Hepha,

Disadvantages:
1.  **Extremely rely on her weapon**, she need her weapon for the critical SP generation
2.  **A bit bad with multiple targets**, even tho the blossom damage is AOE, her weapon can only hit one targets
3.  Her sp problem can be covered really well with Pardo and HB, but **if paired with AE and others, her sp will be much bigger problem** (Though if they decided to release new ice support, it might be fixed)
4.  Even tho she dominates high end abyss, in low end abyss where mobs has low resistance, **her damage against weaker mobs in short time will be low**
(5.  She will **need whole set in order to be competitive**, since everyone will have full HoH)

Hello heki
In fgo, we have

**basic rules**
Different buff multiplies
Class advantage shits

**We have buff**
Type A: (Atk up, defense down)
Type B: (Attack type efficiency up)
Type C: (Crit damage up, ultimate damage up, Extra damage buff that is a status effect, for example extra 50% damage to [King] enemies)
Type D: (Extra damage buff that is included in the ultimate)
Type extra: (Increase atk damage by fixed amount, event damage bonus)

**Bonus buff**
Attribute advantage: (Similar to class advantage but this is hidden and only provides 10% extra damage)
Rng, (from 0.9-1.1, coefficient for damage)
Card order (if an attack chain is started with Buster attack, increase basic damage %, if the attack chain consists of three buster attack add a fixed amount of damage to that chain)

<@503044914016419840> done
__Leader: increase team bleed damage, increase initial SP__


__NA__
Lighsaber four attack, when [beacon] is on field, normal attack also generate kinetic energy

**Holding attack button during fourth attack will do fifth attack**, fifth attack inflict bleed trauma, and it can be connect with third attack afterward


__Evade__
Triggers time fracture upon perfect evasion
Holding evade will enter block mode after first evade


__Special weapon__
Using weapon will summon Beacon which disappear upon exit


__Combo__
When [Beacon] is on field and kinetic energy is full, **click weapon active** consume all energy and summon meteorite, damage and imprison enemies around [Beacon], damage is **treated as both weapon and combo damage.**


__Ult__
**Click ult after using Combo**, cut through the meteorite it summoned, dealing physical damage that is **treated as Bleed damage**
100 SP, 20s cd


__Special__
When summoning [Beacon] or using ultimate, inflict [_Status_], all bleed damage caused by bleed status will have its source moved to character who has the newest [_Status_]

**Team damage caused by using [_Crystal_] which decrease Max HP of stardust enemies has increased TDM%**, fifth attack automatically absorbs all [_Crystal_] on field, **if having at least one [_Crystal_], fifth attack will deal extra physical damage and has increased TDM%**



__QTE__
When enemy is time fractured or bleed
**Fill kinetic energy bar, use weapon active** if not in CD and has SP, decrease switch cd of previous character, can use fifth normal attack if hold attack during QTE
NA

Combo
When [Beacon] is on field and kinetic energy is full, click weapon active consume all energy and summon meteorite, which is treated as both weapon and combo damage


Evade triggers time fracture
Holding evade is block


Ult
Click ult after using Combo, to cut through the meteorite, dealing physical damage that is counted as Bleed damage
